<doc id="256020" wikidata="Q686348" url="?curid=256020" title="Biziura">
<text>Biziura is a genus of stiff-tailed ducks endemic to Australasia and containing one living and one subfossil species.

==Species==
* †&quot;B. delautouri&quot; Forbes, 1892 – New Zealand musk duck – previously endemic to New Zealand, and occurring on both North and South Islands, but now extinct.

