<doc id="256043" wikidata="Q4115904" url="?curid=256043" title="List of science magazines">
<text>A science magazine is a periodical publication with news, opinions, and reports about science, generally written for a non-expert audience. In contrast, a periodical publication, usually including primary research and/or reviews, that is written by scientific experts is called a &quot;scientific journal&quot;. Science magazines are read by non-scientists and scientists who want accessible information on fields outside their specialization.

Articles in science magazines are sometimes republished or summarized by the general press.

==Examples of general science magazines==
